The paper deals with compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The focus of the paper is on estimating the reconstruction error for a sequence of candidate reconstructions, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of random measurement ensembles, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and matrix methods (cs.MM).
